This documentation describes the Evolven Change Analytics Service Broker for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF). The 
Evolven Change Analytics Service Broker for PCF collects inventory and configuration of PCF platform and 
applications running on this platform. It detects changes, drift and inconsistencies in the collected inventory 
and configuration identifying ones that caused or might cause performance and availability issues in PCF 
applications and environment. 


## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

The Evolven Change Analytics Service Broker for PCF includes a configuration collector connecting to PCF and 
regularly scanning the platform and applications running on it identifying changes, drift and inconsistencies
in the configuration. The Service Broker reports collected data to a central Evolven Analytics Server that 
consolidates, cleans, correlates and analyzes all the information collected by the Service Broker in PCF. 
Users can then access the Evolven Analytics Server to interactively review detected changes and differences, 
their risks, impact and correlation to investigated issues. In addition to interactive analysis the users can
set up alerts, reports and other types of notifications to be generated by the Evolven Change Analytics Server
when a risky changes or drift is detected in a particular PCF cluster or across multiple clusters and environments.


## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

Evolven Change Analytics Service Broker for PCF includes the following key features:

* Granular collection of inventory and configuration of applications running in PCF.
* Granular collection of inventory and configuration of PCF platform.
* Detection of actual changes and drift in the configuration of applications and PCF.

